cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on learning visual representations from videos. The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper explores unsupervised learning, which could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of motion-based cues and segmentation could also suggest a connection to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the potential application of the learned features to object detection could place it in the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
